To stress test cpu utilisation, use the command 'yes' in a terminal window.

$ yes

output:

 y
 y
 y

Hit Ctrl-C to stop the program.

To stress more cores in your processor, chain the invocation:

$ yes > /dev/null & yes > /dev/null & yes > /dev/null & ...

Hit Ctrl-C to exist and type:

Type 'killall yes' to destroy the rest.